57096.Name: Runestone of Binding

57989.Description: Bears the Horde symbol... as drawn during the Second War.

58082.Name: Direglob Sample

58224.Description: To the untrained eye, it looks just like any other ordinary ... samophlange.

58490.Name: Opened Mosh'Ogg Bounty
58490.Description: You hear whispering coming from inside.

58492.Name: Disfigured Mosh'Ogg Hand

58501.Name: Quartzite Resin

59036.Name: Crate of Grade-E Meat
59036.Description: Aged, sinewy gorilla meat.  Really only suitable for revenge.

59057.Name: Poobah's Tiara
59057.Description: Specially curved to allow for horns.

59148.Name: Oversized Pirate Hat

59151.Description: Still round, still heavy... still good.

59362.Name: The Legend of Stalvan

59523.Description: For those occasions when regular rum just won't do.

60272.Name: Icon of Pogeyan

60883.Name: Broodqueen Pedipalp

61318.Description: A book of holy spells and blessings.

61974.Description: Observations on wildlife and local resources.

62282.Description: Quite a long time ago, someone was very verbose. Fortunately for you, you don't understand a word of it.

62547.Description: Presumably used for making loin cloths.

62593.Name: Invigorated Silt

62594.Description: Gemstones appear to have been pried from its settings.

63128.Description: Keystone that can complete Troll archaeology artifacts with missing fragments.

64320.Name: Worg Rib

64397.Description: Keystone that can complete Tol'vir archaeology artifacts with missing fragments.

64441.Name: Memory of Zin-Malor

64463.Name: Shard of the Spiritspeaker

64584.Description: To the untrained eye, it looks just like any other ordinary ... samophlange.

65894.Name: Figurine - Dream Owl

65897.Name: Figurine - Earthen Guardian
65897.Description: This tiny statue has been badly damaged.

65900.Description: Light and fine, like powdered silk.

65901.Name: Essence of the Moon-Totem

66939.Description: Surprisingly high quality craftmanship considering the circumstances.

68937.Name: Direhammer's Boots
68937.Description: These boots have seen better days.

69214.Name: Cinderweb Egg

69236.Name: Blueroot Vine
69236.Description: The root is heavy with stored moisture.

69647.Name: Mysterious Gurubashi Bijou

69678.Description: A sizzling piece of stone, wrenched from the chest of one of Ragnaros' elite.

69722.Name: Embergris

69725.Name: Magmolia

71083.Name: Darkmoon Game Token

71634.Description: Allows you to find Darkmoon Artifacts in appropriately-challenging dungeons, raids, and battlegrounds.

71635.Name: Imbued Crystal
71635.Description: Strange threads of power swirl within this rare crystal. Someone at the Darkmoon Faire would probably be interested in acquiring it.

71636.Name: Monstrous Egg
71636.Description: Who knows what creature lurks inside this egg? It would make a great addition to the Darkmoon Faire's collection of rare and amazing creatures.

71637.Name: Mysterious Grimoire
71637.Description: The pages of this ancient book are written in a language you don't recognize. Someone at the Darkmoon Faire would probably be interested in acquiring it.

71638.Name: Ornate Weapon
71638.Description: This weapon seems as beautiful as it is deadly. Someone at the Darkmoon Faire would probably be interested in acquiring it.

71715.Name: A Treatise on Strategy
71715.Description: Anduin Lothar's ultimate compendium of battle strategy. This tome would be of interest to someone at the Darkmoon Faire.

71716.Name: Soothsayer's Runes
71716.Description: An old set of carved fortune-telling runes. Professor Thaddeus Paleo, of the Darkmoon Faire, would be most interested in these.

71951.Name: Banner of the Fallen
71951.Description: Proof of your valor in combat. Someone at the Darkmoon Faire would be interested in this item.

71952.Name: Captured Insignia
71952.Description: Claimed from a defeated opponent. Someone at the Darkmoon Faire would be interested in this item.

71953.Name: Fallen Adventurer's Journal
71953.Description: A journal containing stories of a fallen enemy's epic exploits. Someone at the Darkmoon Faire would be interested in seeing this.

71968.Name: Tonk Scrap
71968.Description: Bits of metal blown off steam tonks in combat.

71974.Name: Fortune
71974.Description: Freshly-penned words spell out the future for those who consult Sayge.

71976.Name: Darkmoon Prize
71976.Description: An oversized stuffed leather toy with shiny eyes and a winning smile.

71977.Name: Darkmoon Craftsman's Kit
71977.Description: A bag containing leather, needles, and patterns for crafting prizes.

71979.Name: Soothsayer's Dust
71979.Description: A glittering, grainy material used to make divining equipment.

72046.Name: Darkblossom
72046.Description: The exact contents of this blend of herbs is only known to members of the Darkmoon Faire.

72050.Name: Sparkling 'Gemstone'
72050.Description: Only an expert would be able to tell the difference between this piece of cut glass and a real gem.

72111.Name: Dry Dogwood Root
72111.Description: Strangely dry and likely very flammable.

72112.Name: Fluttering Breeze
72112.Description: The tighter you hold, the more it tries to slip away.

72118.Name: The Invader's Claw
72118.Description: Far larger than any claw you've ever seen.

72126.Name: Pandemonius' Essence
72126.Description: Looking into the center of the swirling void reveals only further darkness.

72133.Name: Orchard Tool
72133.Description: Not much of a weapon, but better than nothing.

72574.Name: Irradiated Gear
72574.Description: Warning: Prolonged exposure may have undesirable effects, including death.

72578.Name: Nectarbreeze Cider
72578.Description: Sticky, sweet and cloudy. This non-alcoholic variation of the village's famous cider is deemed appropriate for children. And firefighting.

72589.Name: Ripe Orange
72589.Description: Literally bursting with juice - it's no wonder the sprites were after them.

72597.Name: O'mrogg's Warcloth
72597.Description: Dyed with the blood of his victims.

72663.Name: Blinding Fury
72663.Description: Although it does not seem to emit light, it is still blinding.

72706.Name: Rapidly Evolving Frond
72706.Description: It is pulsating with an unnatural ferocity.

72926.Name: Rattan Switch
72926.Description: A thin, pliable, durable piece of wood. Ideal for inflicting pain.

72979.Name: Triple-Bittered Ale
72979.Description: This, you suspect, has very little to do with weapon-making.

73084.Name: Volatile Essence
73084.Description: There's no doubting the raw power contained in this sphere.

73184.Name: Sun Pearl
73184.Description: Intensely hot, you feel energy surge through you upon touching this pearl.

73193.Name: Blushleaf Extract
73193.Description: The extract is a deep blood-red.

73200.Name: Fel Infusion Rod
73200.Description: Used to inject copious amounts of fel fluid.

73269.Name: Great Sea Herring
73269.Description: This little fish looks like it would fit perfectly into a crusty sausage roll.

73368.Name: Tortoise Flank
73368.Description: Tough and meaty. Perfect for jerky.

74160.Name: Zin'Jun's Rifle
74160.Description: There appears to be... 'mud' in the firing mechanism, rendering the weapon useless.

74162.Name: Zin'Jun's Right Eye
74162.Description: By process of elimination, you can assume this to be Zin'Jun's 'shootin' eye'.

74163.Name: Snuff's Corpse
74163.Description: This cat's definitely seen better days.

74246.Name: Cryptomancer's Decoder Ring
74246.Description: Pilfered from the Eye of Eternity, but seemingly inert.

74258.Name: Staff of Pei-Zhi
74258.Description: Somehow sturdy after all these years...

74295.Name: Uprooted Turnip
74295.Description: Dug up, but left behind. Apparently the virmen have little love for turnips.

74296.Name: Stolen Carrot
74296.Description: Slightly gnawed on, but still good!

74297.Name: Pilfered Pumpkin
74297.Description: Plump.  Quite ready to be made into pie.

74298.Name: Dai-Lo Recess Mallet
74298.Description: Heavy and well-crafted. These farmers take their breaks seriously.

74301.Name: Discarded Wood Plank
74301.Description: Looks solid. Really solid actually. Jojo's head might not win this fight.

74615.Name: Paint Soaked Brush
74615.Description: The source of all monkey wisdom.

74616.Name: The Gatewatcher's Talisman
74616.Description: Key to the hidden Empire of Azjol-Nerub.

74623.Name: Emergency Supplies
74623.Description: Lovingly packaged by the Widows of Warriors, Orgrimmar division.

74624.Name: Abandoned Stone Block
74624.Description: These things are rock hard.  Literally.  Jojo may be getting in over his head.

74634.Name: Kun-Pai Ritual Charm
74634.Description: As you pull your hand away from the stone, it feels as though your spirit is sticking to it for a moment.

74752.Name: Solved Cipher
74752.Description: A decoded message from the rogues that infiltrated the red dragonflight!

74755.Name: King Dred's Tooth
74755.Description: This massive tooth would make a decent weapon by itself.

74760.Name: Chipped Ritual Bowl
74760.Description: Concentric circles line the inside of an otherwise plain-looking clay bowl.

74761.Name: Pungent Ritual Candle
74761.Description: Incense, crushed herbs and flecks of minerals have been rolled into the wax, yielding a powerful scent and brilliant flame.

74762.Name: Jade Cong
74762.Description: A square cylinder with elaborate carvings on each face.

74763.Name: Spirit Bottle
74763.Description: An engraving on the bottle reads: 'The body is merely a vessel. The claw seeks what hides within.'

74830.Name: Crystal Tear of Grief
74830.Description: Holding this shard in your hands makes you remember every moment you've ever been sad.

74958.Name: Alliance Medical Supplies
74958.Description: In case of bodily injury, break open.

75023.Name: Pristine Silk Strand
75023.Description: Light refuses to land on this strand of silk.

75202.Name: Speckled Trout
75202.Description: Every bit as slick as it is speckled.

75214.Name: Tidemist Cap
75214.Description: Swollen with moisture, these mushroom caps give off a gentle sheen.

75219.Name: Freshly Fallen Petal
75219.Description: Freshly fallen and of the perfect hue.

75221.Name: Wasp Stinger
75221.Description: A sharp elongated stinger perfect for crafting into a quill.

75256.Name: Pang's Extra-Spicy Tofu
75256.Description: A simply enormous pot of tofu. It's going to be difficult to transport this down the mountain.

75258.Name: Ang's Summer Watermelon
75258.Description: A little unwieldy. It's tough to carry.

75271.Name: Jian
75271.Description: Surprisingly, he seems rather content to be carried around in your bag.

75272.Name: Ling
75272.Description: She is covered with fine, white hair, and a little bit longer than your average pig.

75273.Name: Smelly
75273.Description: He lives up to his name.

75275.Name: Mushan Shoulder Steak
75275.Description: Dark, gamy, muscular meat, from the shoulder. It doesn't look terribly appetizing.

75276.Name: Turtle Meat Scrap
75276.Description: Thickly marbled with fat. Smells a bit gamy.

76100.Name: Wayward Lamb
76100.Description: Scared and trembling. For some reason, this baby sheep doesn't want to go home.

76110.Name: Crate of Fresh Produce
76110.Description: Filled with fruits and vegetables, plucked from the ground this morning.

76115.Name: Amberfly Wing
76115.Description: The iridescent wings sparkle with an unearthly hue.

76173.Name: Bug Leg
76173.Description: They still twitch when you pinch them.

76209.Name: Chunk of Jade
76209.Description: A rough-hewn chunk of stone that looks no worse for the wear.

76298.Name: Stolen Watermelon
76298.Description: The virmen haven't opened any of them yet. Maybe they don't know what's inside?

76333.Name: Green Branch
76333.Description: In the right hands, this'll make for a few good boards.

76337.Name: Stolen Sack of Hops
76337.Description: Mudmug will be wanting this back.

76362.Name: Mudmug's Vial
76362.Description: Used for collecting muddy water from the riverbank.

76483.Name: Scavenged Jade
76483.Description: A hefty burlap sack containing jade trinkets of all shapes and sizes.

76499.Name: Jademoon Leaf
76499.Description: The leaves are covered with a thick, waxy coating.

76501.Name: Emperor Tern Egg
76501.Description: About the size of a chicken egg.

76503.Name: Whitefisher Crane Egg
76503.Description: Large, with a thin, delicate shell.

76516.Name: Hornbill Strider Egg
76516.Description: You know what they say: big egg, big bird.

76761.Name: Pandaren Scroll
76761.Description: A tightly wound scroll, addressed to you.

76973.Name: Sprig of Dreamleaf
76973.Description: A slender branch coated in sticky leaves.

77033.Name: Sack of Grain
77033.Description: Something has been eating away at these grains.

77034.Name: Malted Cave Barley
77034.Description: Slowly malted over time by cave fumes and moisture, these grains of barley hold more natural sweetness than anything you have tasted.

77379.Name: Virmen Tooth
77379.Description: They're surprisingly sharp, for a creature that mostly eats carrots.

77432.Name: Ancient Sutra
77432.Description: Tiny lines of indecipherable text span the pages from cover to cover.

77452.Name: Defender's Arrow
77452.Description: The arrow's feather fletching is stained with blood, but the shaft is unbroken.

77455.Name: Mulberry Leaves
77455.Description: These leaves have been altered through generations of horticulture to produce the perfect silkworm food.

77456.Name: Raw Silk
77456.Description: Fibrous and unkempt, this material is a far cry from the fine garments worn by the Silkmasters.

77471.Name: Spritewater Essence
77471.Description: The water is effervescent and lively.

77954.Name: Vial of Black Dragonsblood
77954.Description: It roils as though alive, and is still warm to the touch.

77955.Name: Alurmi's Vessel
77955.Description: The vessel does not have any buttons, hinges, levers, or other visible controls.

78339.Name: Vial of Preserved Dragonsblood
78339.Description: The vial quivers with constrained energy.

78352.Name: Fragment of Deathwing's Jaw
78352.Description: Merely holding this horrific remnant fills your soul with dread.

78877.Name: Slick Mudfish
78877.Description: Surprisingly well-preserved, but still pretty gross.

78880.Name: Salty Core
78880.Description: Salt from the land, dredged up by the birth of a Weeping Horror.

78881.Name: Chunk of Honeycomb
78881.Description: A cross-section of dark honeycomb oozing with rich, golden honey.

78911.Name: Intact Skitterer Glands
78911.Description: Disgusting to look at and yet the aroma from them is quite healing.

78917.Name: Dojani Orders
78917.Description: A series of crude drawings depict specific mogu artifacts that might be found at the ruins of Dojan.

78918.Name: Imperial Lotus Leaves
78918.Description: A pungent smell comes from these ugly leaves.

78934.Name: The Water of Youth
78934.Description: Just touching the vial is enough to make you feel younger and more vibrant.

78941.Name: Huge Panther Fang
78941.Description: A huge, sharp fang. Hopefully Ken-Ken's new plan is completely different from the last one.

78958.Name: Pillaged Jinyu Loot
78958.Description: A collection of vases, knick knacks, and other assorted goods held precious by those simple folk of the river.

78959.Name: Serpent Egg
78959.Description: Something living slumbers inside. Please handle it carefully.

79025.Name: Slitherscale Harpoon
79025.Description: The shoddy weapon will likely maim its target, not kill it.

79027.Name: Saltback Meat
79027.Description: Tough and salty, just the way your serpent likes its food.

79028.Name: Saltback Meat Scrap
79028.Description: A small scrap of turtle meat.

79046.Name: Sugar Minnow
79046.Description: These small, glass-like fish are sweet to the taste and a favorite of the wild serpents.

79049.Name: Serpentrider Relic
79049.Description: The dusty relic is covered with ancient text. Jenova Longeye at The Arboretum in The Jade Forest will want to see this.

79058.Name: Darkhide's Head
79058.Description: This face is worn with age and stares at you with lifeless, guilt-inducing eyes.

79059.Name: Intact Tortoise Shell
79059.Description: This shell escaped the encounter with you relatively unscathed.

79067.Name: Stolen Egg
79067.Description: A little scuffed but otherwise in good shape.

79120.Name: Mogu Artifact
79120.Description: This seemingly simple relic is covered with dust, worn with age, and seethes with arcane power.

79197.Name: Glade Glimmer
79197.Description: If you were a fish, this would look absolutely mouthwatering.

79198.Name: Spindly Bloodfeather
79198.Description: Not only is it brightly colored, but the blood within the shaft should attract hungry fish.

79237.Name: Enormous Crocolisk Tail
79237.Description: There must be something in the water.

79252.Name: Mogu Poisoned Blade
79252.Description: A dark oil coats this vicious looking blade.

79264.Name: Ruby Shard
79264.Description: This beautiful stone glitters. It would make a lovely gift for Haohan or Tina Mudclaw in the Valley of the Four Winds.

79265.Name: Blue Feather
79265.Description: This soft feather is as blue as the sky. Old Hillpaw or Chee Chee, in the Valley of the Four Winds, may be interested in it.

79266.Name: Jade Cat
79266.Description: An old relic, worn by time. Fish Fellreed or Ella, in the Valley of the Four Winds, may find this valuable.

79267.Name: Lovely Apple
79267.Description: A juicy red apple. Sho or Jogu the Drunk, in the Valley of the Four Winds, may like this.

79268.Name: Marsh Lily
79268.Description: Finding this rare flower is very lucky. Farmer Fung or Gina Mudclaw, in the Valley of the Four Winds, may like this item.

79269.Name: Marsh Lily
79269.Description: Finding this rare flower is very lucky. It would make a lovely present for Gina Mudclaw.

79332.Name: Sentinel Scout's Report
79332.Description: This document is scrawled in the sentinel's flowing hand.

79713.Name: Dynastic Tablet
79713.Description: Ancient text worn with time is etched on this tablet.

79745.Name: Sunwalker Scout's Report
79745.Description: This document is scrawled in the sunwalker's flowing hand.

79753.Name: Slingtail Key
79753.Description: This shiny metal key will free Bold Karasshi and Admiral Taylor.

79806.Name: Arrow for Commander Hsieh
79806.Description: These pandaren arrows are really sharp!

79807.Name: Waterspeaker's Staff
79807.Description: An old, gnarled staff carved with words of power and adorned with assorted relics.

79808.Name: Ceremonial Robes
79808.Description: Silk robes that are covered with runes and symbols.

79809.Name: Jade Crown
79809.Description: A heavy headpiece carved from a single piece of jade.

79810.Name: Rosewood Beads
79810.Description: Polished smooth by years of prayer.

79825.Name: Zhu's Watch Supplies
79825.Description: Grains, herbs, and salted meats are packed neatly inside.

79828.Name: Yak Statuette
79828.Description: For a hozen artifact, it's remarkably well-carved.

79833.Name: Shadelight Truffle
79833.Description: Its glow fades noticeably after being pulled from the ground.

79864.Name: Cindergut Pepper
79864.Description: Spicy enough to burn skin. Make sure you're wearing gloves!

79866.Name: Kunzen Legend-Book
79866.Description: An unbound collection of short stories, hozen proverbs, and offensive pictures.

79867.Name: Fatty Goatsteak
79867.Description: The Kunzen's livestock are nowhere near as gamy as the native goats of the Valley.

79870.Name: Yu-Ping Soup
79870.Description: A soup made out of fish, apples, and herbs.

79875.Name: Song of the Vale
79875.Description: The paper is very old and fragile. The poem is written in strong, elegant brush strokes.

79880.Name: Stolen Supplies
79880.Description: These supplies were slightly damaged in the fighting, but Merchant Shi should have no problem selling them.

79894.Name: Mushan Tail Stew
79894.Description: Prepared the RIGHT way: on a mountain.

79952.Name: Pungent Sprite Needles
79952.Description: These needles have a fresh pine scent to them.

80013.Name: Shademaster Kiryn's Report
80013.Description: Everything appears in order. The request to strap poison bombs to the Hozen does strike you as odd.

80014.Name: Rivett Clutchpop's Report
80014.Description: Straight, to the point, and surprisingly optimistic.

80015.Name: Shokia's Report
80015.Description: Shokia's language, particularly in describing the Hozen, leaves little to be desired.

80061.Name: Riko's Report
80061.Description: While the report lacks any words you are able to make out a drawing of several slickies. You'll just have to fill in the gaps.

80116.Name: Partially Chewed Carrot
80116.Description: Covered in sharp teeth marks. However, these marks look too small to have been made by virmen.

80122.Name: Spideroot
80122.Description: The thorny root stores a sour-tasting liquid.

80133.Name: Preserved Vegetables
80133.Description: Either they didn't like the taste, or they couldn't figure out how to get into the jar.

80134.Name: Uncut Chrysoberyl
80134.Description: The gem slowly shifts from one color to the next as it absorbs the warmth from your hand.

80136.Name: Waxed Plank
80136.Description: A piece of solid bamboo wood.

80137.Name: Ransacked Ring
80137.Description: Perfectly sized for a not-so-dainty pandaren finger.

80138.Name: Stolen Circlet
80138.Description: Someone spent a lot of money on this.

80139.Name: Burglarized Bracelet
80139.Description: It's mostly silver, inlaid with gold and jade.

80140.Name: Bloodbloom
80140.Description: The plant leeches minerals out of the soil, leading to its dark crimson color.

80141.Name: Cave Lily
80141.Description: This beautiful white flower thrives in dark, damp caves.

80142.Name: Ghostcap
80142.Description: This rare mushroom gives off an eerie glow.

80143.Name: Violet Lichen
80143.Description: A rare moss that grows at high altitudes.

80144.Name: Tasty T-Bone
80144.Description: A huge juicy slab of fatty meat.

80176.Name: Water-Damaged Gear
80176.Description: Slightly wet with what you hope is ocean water and not Hozen drool.

80223.Name: Old Hillpaw's Prize Chicken
80223.Description: Upon closer perusal... this IS a really nice chicken.

80228.Name: Enormous Cattail Grouper Tooth
80228.Description: It's pristine - suitable for use in a necklace or bracelet.

80230.Name: Cast Iron Pot
80230.Description: Coated with years of yak grease.

80231.Name: Goldenfire Orchid
80231.Description: You'll have to handle this delicately - it's quite fragile.

80236.Name: Apple-Berry Hooch
80236.Description: Best drank out of a paper bag.

80240.Name: Strange Spherical Stone
80240.Description: A rough sphere carved from the native rock of Pandaria.

80241.Name: Muskpaw's Keepsake
80241.Description: This simple bracelet has symbols of love and affection carved into it.

80245.Name: Kun-Lai Meaty Bits
80245.Description: It's not important where it came from. What's important is, it's meat - or passes for it, at least.

80260.Name: Dojani Eel
80260.Description: Probably best not to hold it for too long.

80262.Name: Beloved Ring
80262.Description: The intials J.H. are inscribed on the inside of the ring.

80294.Name: Mogu Relic
80294.Description: This should fetch a few coins.

80295.Name: Packet of Green Cabbage Seeds
80295.Description: A paper envelope that rattles when you shake it.

80307.Name: Grummlepack
80307.Description: A collection of satchels, bags, boxes, and various parcels strewn together with string and rope weighing many more times that of a Grummle. The smell of incense and yak musk permeate every inch of these items.

80308.Name: Fire Lotus Incense
80308.Description: This highly potent fragrance will rouse even the most reluctant individual to acts of bravery.

80310.Name: Silver Goby
80310.Description: The fish around here have very strange taste in food.

80311.Name: Filled Oil Vial
80311.Description: A dark, foul-smelling substance sloshes about in this vial.

80312.Name: Empty Oil Vial
80312.Description: This empty grummle vial smells of wet yak and jasmine.

80314.Name: EZ-Gro Green Cabbage
80314.Description: Your first harvest! They won't fetch anything at the market, but their sentimental value is PRICELESS.

80315.Name: Stolen Supplies
80315.Description: This bundle contains mostly intact trade goods of various origin.

80316.Name: Lucky Virmen's Foot
80316.Description: This virmen foot has seen better days. The fur is worn and stained.

80317.Name: Lucky Yak Shoe
80317.Description: This rusty old yak shoe doesn't feel very lucky...

80318.Name: Lucky Four Winds Clover
80318.Description: The leaves on this clover are mysteriously pristine.

80319.Name: Lucky "Gold" Coin
80319.Description: This coin has seen many journeys with Ji-Lu, but is almost unrecognizable due to tarnish.

80437.Name: Armored Carp
80437.Description: Thick, heavy scales cover the fish.

80535.Name: Yeti Shackle Key
80535.Description: This mishappen piece of metal should work to unfasten Old Poot Poot's shackles.

80598.Name: Zhen's Banner
80598.Description: You have regained the shado-master's honor.

80677.Name: Emerald Tailfeather
80677.Description: A long, silky, dazzlingly green feather.

80679.Name: Dusky Tailfeather
80679.Description: The color shifts from indigo to violet as the sun reflects upon the quill.

80685.Name: Spare Plank
80685.Description: Lash enough of these together, and you'll have a pretty sturdy raft.

80804.Name: Tough Kelp
80804.Description: Elastic enough to bend, strong enough to hold.

80806.Name: Broken Bamboo Stalk
80806.Description: Sharp enough to effectively poke things.

80810.Name: Shark Fillet
80810.Description: Far too much meat for one person to eat. What could Wise Ana Wu want with all this meat?

80830.Name: Rusty Shipwreck Debris
80830.Description: Not sure how he expects to make bomb's with this junk.

80831.Name: Snapclaw's Claw
80831.Description: He won't be snapping anymore, that's for sure.

80907.Name: Opalescent Blue Crab Shell
80907.Description: When held to the light, this shell has a particularly gorgeous sheen.

80938.Name: Gift of the Great Crane
80938.Description: On the outside, simply a feather... but within, it bears a sacred power.

80944.Name: Bundle of Kafa'kota Berries
80944.Description: Stuffed with a hundred Kafa'kota Berries.

81054.Name: Kafa'kota Berry
81054.Description: These unassuming little berries pack a lot of power.

81116.Name: Suncrawler
81116.Description: The fish around here sure have strange taste.

81122.Name: Wolf Piranha
81122.Description: Careful, you might lose a finger on this one.

81137.Name: Rabbitsfoot's Luckydo
81137.Description: This ancient preserved rabbit's foot reeks of various oils, incense, and an assortment of animal odors that curl the nose.

81174.Name: Dark Pitch
81174.Description: The dark resin is thick, gooey, and very flammable.

81176.Name: Mist-Shaman's Torch
81176.Description: Used to break the mistlurkers to the yaungol shaman's will.

81178.Name: Stone Key
81178.Description: The oddly-shaped key is carved from a hard, dark stone.

81183.Name: Flask of Kafa
81183.Description: Apparently "seconds from being torn apart by a yeti" wasn't enough of an emergency for Burrberry.

81261.Name: Stolen Pandaren Spices
81261.Description: These strongly aromatic spices give pandaren incense its unique scent.

81269.Name: Waterfall-Polished Stone
81269.Description: Falling water has beaten this stone perfectly smooth.

81293.Name: Stolen Luckydos
81293.Description: This bag is filled with grummle lucky charms and reeks of incense and scented oils.

81355.Name: Palewind Totem
81355.Description: The ancient totem was carved by hand. It is covered in symbols and drawings that you cannot read.

81385.Name: Stolen Inkgill Ritual Staff
81385.Description: An ancient staff, used to bind the souls of the Inkgill to their pearls, and thus, the Mere.

81393.Name: Chen's Full Keg
81393.Description: Completely filled with Chen's brew, "The Emperor".

81713.Name: Blind Rage Essence
81713.Description: A ball of oily blackness with smoke emanating from it.

81741.Name: Blinding Rage Trap
81741.Description: Black smoke seeps from the center of this trap.

81890.Name: Blood-Revealed Map
81890.Description: Zandalari blood has splashed onto the worn paper revealing what appears to be a map.

81892.Name: Torn Page
81892.Description: A series of intricate symbols decorate the page.

82298.Name: Handful of Volatile Blooms
82298.Description: Even the smell of the red-hued blooms burns your nose.

82299.Name: Blood-Stained Blade
82299.Description: Dried remenants of previous battles cover the blade of this weapon.

82342.Name: Violet Citron
82342.Description: The pollen from these flowers has a strangely acidic, citrusy smell.

82387.Name: Full Mushan Bladder
82387.Description: This seems like a GREAT thing to put in your bag.

82388.Name: Rankbite Shell Fragment
82388.Description: Tough, scaly, and regularly shaped. Perfect for mail armor.

82389.Name: Mao-Willow
82389.Description: The flowering branches are light, fluffy, and prickly to the touch.

82393.Name: Shen Dynasty Rubbing
82393.Description: The text on the tablet was so worn it is hard to make out the symbols on the rubbing.

82394.Name: Qiang Dynasty Rubbing
82394.Description: Deeply carved symbols on the tablet have made this rubbing the easiest to read.

82395.Name: Wai Dynasty Rubbing
82395.Description: This rubbing contains only a small piece of the broken tablet's writing.

82605.Name: Corrupted Insignia
82605.Description: This small insignia marks the bearer as a member of the Dark Shaman.

82722.Name: Krik'thik Limb
82722.Description: Tiny holes in the hard shell are secreting some kind of caustic substance.

173025.Description: A heavy scroll compiling the professional works of master Kyrian crafters.

173026.Name: Omni Electromagnetic Amplifier
173026.Description: Radiation based detection for use with only the most advanced neural networks.

173028.Name: Flux Energized Servos
173028.Description: Precision movement for use with only the most advanced neural networks.

173060.Name: Aerated Water
173060.Description: Used for mixing various pigments into inks. Sold by inscription vendors.

173187.Name: River Sediment
173187.Description: Altogether unassuming. If you squint hard enough you think you might see a sparkle, but it could just as easily be a trick of the light.

173202.Name: Shrouded Cloth
173202.Description: Gathered from killing creatures. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

173268.Name: Fresh Gorm Gris
173268.Description: Pretty, for something that just came out of a gormling.

173269.Name: Training Gem
173269.Description: Used to help train phalynx's laser location skills.

173285.Name: Treasonous Missive
173285.Description: Penned by Lord Andrei of House Iremoore.

173287.Name: Medallion of Desire
173287.Description: Once worn by the Countess, this medallion seethes with power.

173307.Name: Reinforced Armor
173307.Description: Sturdy replacement armor fitted for a phalynx.

173354.Name: Spear of Kalliope
173354.Description: It is arguably the most impressive spear you have encountered.

173690.Name: Cloudstrider Antler
173690.Description: The perfect toy for a larion to chew on.

173696.Name: Venthyr Ritual Dagger
173696.Description: Has aided countless souls without ever piercing flesh.

173697.Name: Venthyr Ritual Tome
173697.Description: Each ritual is endlessly detailed with countless variations.

173732.Name: Strange Runestone
173732.Description: A strange rune has been brutally chipped into the stone.

173733.Name: Sinstone Records
173733.Description: A complete archive would detail in explicit detail every sinstone the venthyr have ever accumulated.

173737.Name: Temel's Body
173737.Description: Cracked all over. The Chamberlain's goons roughed him up bad.

173738.Name: Temel's Wings
173738.Description: One is slightly larger than the other.

173739.Name: Temel's Head
173739.Description: Frozen in a state of wild cackling.

173798.Name: Battered Journal
173798.Description: Several pages appear to be missing.

173800.Name: Featureless Mask
173800.Description: A strange mask worn by the hostile fae.

173810.Name: Darksight Potion
173810.Description: Unusually light and cold to the touch, with a smell reminiscent of rotted carcass.

173880.Name: Purified Metal
173880.Description: The smelting process seems to have removed all trace of the Forsworn's magic.

173882.Name: Soulsteel Clamps
173882.Description: A special pair of clamps with a soulsteel core, capable of holding true against massive force.

173909.Name: Sparkling Driftglobe Core
173909.Description: Reacts to the heat of an anima brazier to create a driftglobe used for precise smithing.

173910.Name: Gracepetal Incense Burner
173910.Description: Mikanikos describes the smell as "inspirational". He cannot work without it.

173954.Name: Maddened Writings
173954.Description: It's probably not a good idea to be reading this.

173956.Name: Coalesced Corruption
173956.Description: You don't want to know where the eyeballs came from.

173976.Name: Medallion of Envy
173976.Description: Bestowed upon Venthyr by The Sire himself. Allows the wearer to exert partial dominion over Revendreth.

174043.Name: Phylactery of Arin'gore
174043.Description: The tiny dagger is plainly worked without ornamentation.

174061.Name: Phaestus, Genesis of Aeons
174061.Description: Blessed instrument of the First Forgelite, conduit in the creation of the first centurions and the Spires of Ascension.

174063.Name: Titan Core
174063.Description: A titan core taken from Ra-den.

174064.Name: Titan Core
174064.Description: A titan core taken from Ra-den.

174065.Name: Titan Core
174065.Description: A titan core taken from Ra-den.

174072.Name: Raw Meat
174072.Description: Raw, bloodied meat. Not edible. Don't even try.

174074.Name: Cooked Meat
174074.Description: This meat greatly benefits from the cheapest seasoning of all: hunger.

174080.Name: Faceless Mask of the Long Night
174080.Description: Fear of the unknown is a lesser beings' weakness.

174083.Name: Faceless Mask of the Burned Bridge
174083.Description: Nothing left but the faint smell of smoke and a memory of eyes watering.

174092.Name: Mateo's Mirror Shard
174092.Description: Entrusted to Sinkeeper Mateo before the Curator was cast into the Maw. Can be combined with Emil's shard to complete the Curator's mirror.

174093.Name: Ionata's Fangs
174093.Description: Fangs once belonging to Examiner Ionata.

174094.Name: Boian's Fangs
174094.Description: Fangs once belonging to Examiner Boian.

174095.Name: Daciana's Fangs
174095.Description: Fangs once belonging to Examiner Daciana.

174098.Name: Death Lotus Powder
174098.Description: A powder made from ground up death lotus, among other things. Known for its use in venthyr spells.

174100.Name: Stonebreaker Mallet
174100.Description: Used by dredgers to break down stone.

174101.Name: Valuable Salvage
174101.Description: Old and worn, might still be useful.

174102.Name: Anima Canister
174102.Description: The anima within is struggling to escape.

174111.Name: Medallion of Avarice
174111.Description: Bestowed upon Venthyr by The Sire himself. Allows the wearer to exert partial dominion over Revendreth.

174210.Name: Anima Globule
174210.Description: Though clearly liquid, it somehow manages to keep its form when held.

174211.Name: Maldraxxian Weapon
174211.Description: Infused with strange necrotic powers... this should not be in Revendreth.

174219.Name: Stolen Memento
174219.Description: A lost possession, left behind with the death of the grove.

174269.Name: Heart of Tirna Noch
174269.Description: Simmering with stored anima, the last remnants of a great tree.

174330.Name: Perfected Circlet Mold
174330.Description: A mold of perfect circular shape. Used by Mikanikos to finely craft circular components.

174336.Name: Crimson Cravat
174336.Description: The final touch to pull an ensemble together.

174357.Name: Death Lotus Petal
174357.Description: Can be crushed into a powder to ward off curses.

174377.Name: Volume of Victory
174377.Description: A single book of the seemingly endless volumes of victory.

174450.Name: Amathet Artifact
174450.Description: A clue to the history of the mysterious Amathet tol'vir.

174454.Name: The Countess's Sinstone
174454.Description: Every venthyr who lived a past life has a sinstone. The Countess hid hers, insisting she was born of the Shadowlands.

174467.Name: Bulging Digestive Sac
174467.Description: Filled with a green, acrid fluid. It's sloshing. A lot.

174498.Name: Seal of Contrition
174498.Description: Once used in the penitential process for souls arriving in Revendreth, it was cast aside long ago for more brutal methods.

174499.Name: Empowered Bones
174499.Description: Bones from a construct imbued with anima.

174747.Name: Mogu Armament
174747.Description: Though far too heavy and off-balance for most to wield, these weapons can be wielded with devastating force by the mogu.

174774.Name: Wastewander Supplies
174774.Description: Valuable resources for the Wastewanders' fight against the aqir.

174776.Name: Goliath Trophy
174776.Description: This thing is as heavy as it is slimy.

174777.Name: The Curse of Stone
174777.Description: The bindings glow with curious symbols. A number of pages appear to be missing.

174780.Name: Emptied First Aid Kit
174780.Description: A useful carrying case for supplies, even if no medkits are left.

174782.Name: Fear and Flesh
174782.Description: The battered, leather-bound book is in poor condition.

174783.Name: Torn Page of "Fear and Flesh"
174783.Description: Portions of the text are blotted with dark liquid, some of which is smeared across the lower half of the page.

174784.Name: The Final Truth
174784.Description: Hidden behind thin striations of water-streaked dust, the work appears to be largely illegible.

174785.Name: Torn Page of "The Final Truth"
174785.Description: Symbols move about the page in an unidentifiable, yet mesmerising pattern.

174821.Name: Incense of Guidance
174821.Description: Used by aspirants to guide their way during their final trial.

174867.Name: Shard of Corruption
174867.Description: A thick miasma of corruption seeps from the shard. It feels incredibly heay, and holding it imparts an overwhelming feeling of oppression and iniquity.

174908.Name: Dragon Heart
174908.Description: A dragon heart taken from Vexiona.

174909.Name: Dragon Heart
174909.Description: A dragon heart taken from Vexiona.

174910.Name: Dragon Heart
174910.Description: A dragon heart taken from Vexiona.

174911.Name: Prophetic Eye
174911.Description: A prophetic eye taken from Il'gynoth, Corruption Reborn.

174912.Name: Prophetic Eye
174912.Description: A prophetic eye taken from Il'gynoth, Corruption Reborn.

174913.Name: Prophetic Eye
174913.Description: A prophetic eye taken from Il'gynoth, Corruption Reborn.

174916.Name: Withering Hemlock
174916.Description: The roots of this plant contain potent poison, if you know how to mix it properly.

174930.Name: Inquisitor Stelia's Sinstone
174930.Description: A long list of murderous sins.

174947.Name: Old Grimoire
174947.Description: It's always dangerous to try to bend a voidwalker to your will. But this grimoire should allow you to do so... as long as you have the power to see the ritual through.

174968.Name: Veil Blossom
174968.Description: Veil Blossoms are only known for being annoying weeds. There is no known medicinal usage for them.

174993.Name: Crystallized Void
174993.Description: Void energy radiates off of the fragment.

174996.Name: Solar Emanator
174996.Description: Though inactive, the device is still warm to the touch.

175003.Name: Zan-tien Generator Part
175003.Description: A piece of a generator used by the Zan-tien to accelerate the hatching of Cloud Serpent eggs.

175020.Name: Amathet Figurine
175020.Description: A stone effigy to one of the gods worshipped by the Amathet.

175023.Name: Vial of Purified Anima
175023.Description: Extracted from the living by the Dokani mogu, then distilled into its purest form.

175058.Name: Black Empire Armament
175058.Description: Crafted from otherworldly metals, both feather-light and durable.

175059.Name: Otherworldly Saddle
175059.Description: It certainly has a lot of spikes.

175138.Name: Sealed Scroll of Soul Rot
175138.Description: The magic inside the scroll wants to be let out, but you refrain from tearing apart the parchment.

175139.Name: Mischief-touched Anima
175139.Description: Something's a little off about this anima.

175149.Name: A Small Carving of Ysera
175149.Description: Rough edges smoothed by time and handling, the ancient wood carving has been preserved by high quality protection spells.

175151.Name: Fearbreaker
175151.Description: The ancestral hammer of the Bronzebeard clan.

175152.Name: A Slime-Covered Book of Secrets
175152.Description: Surprisingly, the gorm matriarch's digestive juices haven't had much effect on the book's protections.

175154.Name: A Secret Never Spoken
175154.Description: Sealed so it cannot be read aloud.

175275.Name: Scroll of the Path
175275.Description: A carefully inscribed scroll that tells the history of an aspirant becoming a Kyrian.

175384.Name: Glass Shard
175384.Description: A small piece of reflective glass with jagged, sharp edges.

175410.Name: Dreadshade Extract
175410.Description: A highly versatile, potentially deadly reagent.

175413.Name: Anima Vial
175413.Description: A small vial of condensed anima often used for barter with brokers.

175753.Name: Life-Hardened Anima
175753.Description: The hard core of a spent chrysalis. The anima has almost crystallized, but glimmers with potential.

175756.Name: Medallion of Dominion
175756.Description: Its immense power passively pulls in anima from the air around it.

175770.Name: Medallion of Dread
175770.Description: Bestowed upon Venthyr by The Sire himself. Allows the wearer to exert partial dominion over Revendreth.

175791.Name: Ariella's Wing
175791.Description: Not a single feather is out of place.

175792.Name: Larion Flight Feather
175792.Description: Pristine plumage from a larion's wing.

175795.Name: Betrayer's Eye
175795.Description: The truth lingers inside it still.

175840.Name: A Light Snack
175840.Description: This will certainly give Stonehead a tummy ache.

175886.Name: Dark Parchment
175886.Description: A thicker stock than normal parchment, it can be lightly engraved by a Scribe.

175967.Name: Etherwyrm Filament
175967.Description: Surprisingly strong anima-infused strands from an etherwyrm's tail.

175968.Name: Animyllis Bloom
175968.Description: The extremely pungent bloom of the Animyllis bulb.

175975.Name: Meredy's Spell Book
175975.Description: Meredy's spell book is soaked in water, but most of the pages are still legible.

175979.Name: Ice Mote
175979.Description: This mote is cold to the touch and hums with magical power.

175980.Name: Old Spring
175980.Description: A little shine will make this spring last for a while.

175981.Name: Rusted Chain
175981.Description: You could break this chain apart to create something sharp enough for a trap.

176052.Name: Iron Skull Belt Buckle
176052.Description: You may call it gaudy. Venthyr call it fashion.

176053.Name: Pleated Cape
176053.Description: The perfect touch of drama that every venthyr needs.

176054.Name: Thigh High Boots
176054.Description: Molded perfectly for somebody. That somebody is not you.

176055.Name: Lace-Up Bracers
176055.Description: Ask a tortured soul to lace yours today!

176397.Name: Dredhollow Bolt
176397.Description: Can be brought to Wingsmash in the Banewood.

176760.Name: Buzzkill's Stinger
176760.Description: Seems perfect for gormsmithing, you guess.

176805.Name: Centurion Armor Fragment
176805.Description: Metal of this caliber is hard to find, of late.

176806.Name: Drained Anima-Core
176806.Description: Dimly lit. It contains very little power.

177061.Name: Twilight Bark
177061.Description: Gathered by Miners from Phaedrum Deposits in Ardenweald.

177186.Name: Forgotten Memorandum
177186.Description: A fragment of a larger story.

177693.Name: Requisitioner's Scroll
177693.Description: A long scroll detailing the recent acquisitions for the House of the Chosen.

177710.Name: Patrol Schedule
177710.Description: The master copy of the current patrol schedule for the House of the Chosen guards.

177712.Name: Envoy's Letter
177712.Description: Correspondence between the House of the Chosen and the House of Rituals.

177818.Name: Dark Mojo
177818.Description: This dark mojo animated the nearby undead of Nazmir towards the essence of Mueh'zala.

177844.Name: Plague Sample
177844.Description: A small glass tube filled with a bright liquid. There's markings on the glass that appear to be notation. Marileth will likely want it.

177878.Name: Animacone
177878.Description: The seed pulses gently with a dark, blue energy.

177879.Name: Maldraxxi Bone Marrow
177879.Description: This bone marrow was mined from within Maldraxxus. Best not to think about it.

177881.Name: Nadjia's Sinstone
177881.Description: The abhorrent actions of Viscountess Eak'le of Asquiron, premiere of the Order of Blades are described herein.

177954.Name: Condensed Anima Mote
177954.Description: A fraction of what the extractor was capable of producing, in better times.

177957.Name: Necessary Enhancers
177957.Description: A special formula to improve one's combat abilities.

177958.Name: Duskwood Report
177958.Description: The blood-soaked parchment lacks detail, but stresses the need for immediate reinforcements.

177959.Name: Redridge Report
177959.Description: Hastily written notes detailing a rise in the Scourge's presence.

177960.Name: Elwynn Report
177960.Description: A brief report on encounters against the Scourge.

178018.Name: The Brand's Key
178018.Description: The initials 'BtB' are carved onto the key, inside what looks like the shape of a... heart?

178019.Name: Additional Volumes of Victory
178019.Description: A single book of the seemingly endless volumes of victory.

178020.Name: Volume of Victory: Vol 1
178020.Description: The first volume of the seemingly endless volumes of victory.

178138.Name: Harp Piece
178138.Description: A remnant of a shattered harp, once used to soothe silkstriders.

178144.Name: Raw Silkstrider Silk
178144.Description: Beautiful silk strands, fresh from the silkstrider.

178150.Name: Tasty Purian
178150.Description: One of the Stewards' favorite foods.

178170.Name: Vernon's Field Report
178170.Description: A compilation of field officers' notes, detailing the return of the Scourge.

178215.Name: Leafy Loam
178215.Description: Smells musty, but not entirely unpleasant.

178229.Name: Herbert's Spell Book
178229.Description: Herbert's spellbook has several pages with notes that include, "not dangerous enough", "too safe", and "too crazy to not work."

178465.Name: Giant Silk Bundle
178465.Description: A huge bundle of silk, freshly spun from the lonely matriarch.

178526.Name: Lost Cryptkeeper's Ring
178526.Description: Cryptkeeper Kassir will be pleased to have this again.

178558.Name: Afflictor's Key
178558.Description: Etched with runes matching those on the locks that bind Anduin in the Tremaculum.

178565.Name: Suspicious Message
178565.Description: Crumpled parchment covered with fine calligraphy "NOOS SEOG EHTIT".

178569.Name: The Origin of Death
178569.Description: A dense tome pondering the creation of the interwoven mechanisms of the Shadowlands and how they relate to one another.

178570.Name: Fading Memory Glass
178570.Description: This memory glass appears to be very old, and the memories within will soon be lost.

178571.Name: A Slimy Correspondence
178571.Description: A letter from Margrave Stradama to an unknown recipient, it is written in a coded language you are not able to decipher.

178572.Name: Ring of Otherworldly Metal
178572.Description: A ring of strange metal that appears similar to the makeup of Oribos.

178573.Name: Unusual Automaton Parts
178573.Description: Appears to be pieces from the core of an automaton, but unlike any that you've seen in the Shadowlands.

178574.Name: Strange Ritual Mask
178574.Description: A mask depicting a robotic face unlike anything you've seen in the Shadowlands.

178575.Name: Golden Orb of Energy
178575.Description: An intricate and complicated golden orb-like structure surrounding a dark interior. It periodically flickers with white energy, but never for long.

178576.Name: Ancient Broker Headpiece
178576.Description: The headpiece of a broker of unknown origin, it looks significantly different than the brokers you've met in Oribos.

178577.Name: Nalthor's Phylactery Instructions
178577.Description: Instructions on the creation of a phylactery, a necromantic ritual that liches rarely share with others.

178578.Name: Strange Doll
178578.Description: Appears to be a child's doll or plaything, oddly-shaped and likely from a place outside of Azeroth.

178579.Name: Stradama's Lost Ledger
178579.Description: A series of meticulously-maintained lists of objects and the slime pools in which they are stored, using a coordinate system the likes of which you've never seen.

178580.Name: Champion's Coin
178580.Description: A curious coin granted to champions of the Theater of Pain when they win a certain number of bouts. Not useful as a currency, only for ceremonial purposes.

178581.Name: Engorged Gorm Larva
178581.Description: A squishy, wiggling gorm larva that looks ready to mature at any moment.

178582.Name: Golden Death Mask
178582.Description: A mask depicting Mueh'zala's visage, likely from a civilization that once worshipped him.

178583.Name: Tome of Dredger Alchemy
178583.Description: A book detailing a variety of methods for the creation and use of dredgers.

178584.Name: Medallion of Orientation
178584.Description: A medallion used to orient oneself in the Shadowlands relative to Oribos. Valuable for a general leading an army, but invaluable for travelling traders.

178594.Name: Anima-bound Wraps
178594.Description: Anima infused wraps that add strength to bones and flesh.

178655.Name: Lye's Ritual Drafts
178655.Description: Plans for the construction of Mor'Bitan's ritual.

178656.Name: Xeeli's Ritual Drafts
178656.Description: Plans for the construction of Mor'Bitan's ritual.

178657.Name: Halen's Ritual Drafts
178657.Description: Plans for the construction of Mor'Bitan's ritual.

178662.Name: Unfinished Blade
178662.Description: A blade with no hilt. The runes embedded in the metal seem to call out to you.

178676.Name: Pulsating Hide Scraps
178676.Description: This skin is dripping what you can only assume is the blood of the land itself.

178681.Name: Slim Shinbone
178681.Description: A thin bone used to pry open crates or locked chests!

178684.Name: Maldracite Dust
178684.Description: A fine maldracite powder used to draw runes.

178717.Name: Ardenmoth Cocoon
178717.Description: A moth in hand is worth two in the trees. Probably.

178876.Name: Sack of Supplies
178876.Description: Contains plenty of raw materials for the artisans at Glitterfall Basin.

178898.Name: Pungent Swarmer Toxin
178898.Description: Smells strongly of spoiled fruit and excrement.

178903.Name: Spriggan-Sized Weaponry
178903.Description: Just as deadly as the normal version.

178904.Name: Shackle Key
178904.Description: Despite being exposed to the elements, the key remains remarkably unscathed.

178915.Name: Ripe Purian
178915.Description: A perfectly ripe, extremely aromatic purian fruit. It will probably spoil shortly.

178995.Name: Soul Mirror Shard
178995.Description: The Forsworn collect these shards in an attempt to recapture their past memories.

179008.Name: Depleted Goliath Core
179008.Description: The heart of any Goliath, these cores keep them powered with anima.

179009.Name: Tampered Anima Charger
179009.Description: Used to empower Forsworn Centurions past their normal limits.

179010.Name: Overcharged Goliath Core
179010.Description: Allows the capture of Kalisthene's memory.

179024.Name: Medallion of Pride
179024.Description: Bestowed upon Venthyr by The Sire himself. Allows the wearer to exert partial dominion over Revendreth.

179317.Name: Bonemetal
179317.Description: A dense, but pliable, metal used in the construction of arms and armor.

179318.Name: Sorrowvine
179318.Description: A hateful vine that grows only in the lowlands of Revendreth.

179320.Name: Wealdwood
179320.Description: Shaped wood enchanted by the keepers of Ardenweald.

179321.Name: Gildenite
179321.Description: A hard, golden material used for many purposes.

179327.Name: Coin of Brokerage
179327.Description: A highly-valued coin of the Shadowlands used to trade for rare materials with the Brokers.

179378.Name: Soul Mirror
179378.Description: Used to capture a memory of a target for training purposes in the Path of Ascension.

179922.Name: Animacone
179922.Description: A seed of condensed anima, fallen from one of the celestial trees. It's covered in saliva.

180010.Name: Meaty Crab Chunk
180010.Description: A meaty hunk of crab meat, fresh and filling.

180025.Name: Pile of Blubberfat
180025.Description: A thick and well-insulated pile of fat taken from a great seal.

180035.Name: Eye of the Scryer
180035.Description: A glowing, still twitching eye, pried directly from Leerok the Scryer.

180050.Name: Wither Blade
180050.Description: The edge is stained with the blood of the High Chieftain.

180126.Name: Drained Wildseed
180126.Description: This wildseed's anima is almost completely drained, but the spirit within is still surviving.

180172.Name: Animacone
180172.Description: Some anima still remains within this animacone.

180231.Name: Razor Hill Report
180231.Description: Details of the Scourge attacks at Razor Hill.

180232.Name: Dranosh'ar Blockade Report
180232.Description: A slim report on a few encounters with the Scourge.

180233.Name: Far Watch Post Report
180233.Description: The tattered, blood-soaked parchment is difficult to read.

180279.Name: Sinstone Fragment
180279.Description: Contains a detailed account of mortal sins.

180281.Name: Sinstone Fragment
180281.Description: Contains a detailed account of mortal sins.

180282.Name: Sinstone Fragment
180282.Description: Contains a detailed account of mortal sins.

180283.Name: Sinstone Fragment
180283.Description: Contains a detailed account of mortal sins.

180284.Name: Sinstone Fragment
180284.Description: Contains a detailed account of mortal sins.

180296.Name: Shrouded Necromancer Head
180296.Description: Spies lurk in the shadows of the Ember Court. Baroness Vashj will be interested in this. (|cfff2e699+Bonus Happiness|r)

180447.Name: Animacone
180447.Description: A seed of condensed anima, fallen from one of the celestial trees.

180448.Name: Eroded Heat Sink
180448.Description: Absorbs heat energy produced  by bastion constructs.

180449.Name: Failed Experiment
180449.Description: Its design is complex and obtuse. No discernible use could be derived upon examination.

180450.Name: Assorted Bolts
180450.Description: A pile of extra bolts... they must go to something! Right?

180451.Name: Grand Inquisitor's Sinstone Fragment
180451.Description: Archivist Fane needs these to recreate Grand Inquisitor Sinstones, which will allow you to hunt the most dangerous inquisitors in the Halls of Atonement.

180452.Name: Spear of Kalliope
180452.Description: It is arguably the most impressive spear you have encountered.

180462.Name: Mask of Possession
180462.Description: This unused mask appears to be dormant and safe to wear.

180466.Name: Forged Permission Slip
180466.Description: You have added enough blobs of sealing wax that you're sure this will work.

180470.Name: Wild Fungus
180470.Description: It might be delicious. It might kill you. Picky Stefan will be interested in this. (|CFF1b8729+Humble|R)

180481.Name: Curious Blueprint
180481.Description: It seems to detail a piece of equipment.

180484.Name: Noko's Flute
180484.Description: The traveling flute of an ancient caravan. (|CFFfbdd52+Exciting|R)

180485.Name: Ansel's Lucky Violin
180485.Description: Lucky or not, this is a beautiful instrument. (|CFFfbdd52+Exciting|R)

180486.Name: Chiu's Lute
180486.Description: The back of the neck is covered in pandaren etchings. (|CFFfbdd52+Exciting|R)

180543.Name: Wild Gorm Gris
180543.Description: More potent than the domestic-grown variety.

180606.Name: Ara'lon's Report
180606.Description: A written account of the events that transpired near Blackthorn Grove.

180774.Name: Preserved Berries
180774.Description: These dried berries are wrinkled and scorched. They were collected from a dead world.

192753.Name: The Scales of Wrath
192753.Description: A savagely poignant rebuttal of the order imposed by the aspects and their titan allies. Told from the point of view of a protodrake who would eventually feel forced to rebel after being pushed to the edges of draconic society.

192754.Name: Dracuixote
192754.Description: The story of an ancient green dragon who could no longer tell his dreams from the waking world. Accompanied by a long suffering dragonspawn, Dracuixote embarks on a fanciful quest to restore an imagined golden age.

192755.Name: The Lord of the Wings
192755.Description: A band of hardened drakonid and plucky whelps come together to destroy an artifact of terrible power that can only be undone in the forges of the mad aspect who created it.

192756.Name: The Red and the Black Flights
192756.Description: A low-born black drake fails to reconcile his militaristic heritage with his respect for intelligence and wit, eventually falling to despair over unrequited love and the materialism rampant among dragonkind.

192757.Name: Pride and Protodrakes
192757.Description: The quintessential love story. Set in a time before the aspects, an up-and-coming young protodrake runs afoul of a standoffish elder. Their animosity turns to appreciation and, eventually, love as they come to understand each other.

192758.Name: Coil of Heavy Rope

192759.Name: Magmasworn Spear

194716.Description: A report detailing the safety of the western coastline.

194728.Name: Fiery Spirit
194728.Description: The essence of passion, taken from an elemental of great spirit.

194729.Name: Fiery Spirit
194729.Description: The essence of passion, taken from an elemental of great spirit.

194730.Name: Scalebelly Mackerel
194730.Description: A common fish found across the Dragon Isles. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

194746.Name: Thomas's Empty Bottle
194746.Description: A perfect vessel for Miguel's gift.

194747.Description: The poison producing organ of a giant spider. Tuskarr are known to mix it together to create powerful medicines for spider venom.
