194767.Description: A frosted rune crafted by players with the Inscription skill. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

194846.Name: Blazing Ink
194846.Description: A fiery ink crafted by players with the Inscription skill. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

194874.Name: Scribe's Fastened Quill
194874.Description: This quill will work in lieu of a Virtuoso Inking Set.

194900.Name: Miva's Dispelling Wand
194900.Description: This wand was specially developed by the Kirin Tor for their excursion to the Azure Span. It can dispel small fields of unstable arcane energy.

194901.Name: Curved Horns
194901.Description: These sturdy horns have seen much combat over the years.

194966.Name: Thousandbite Piranha
194966.Description: A common fish native to freshwater around the Dragon Isles. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

194967.Name: Aileron Seamoth
194967.Description: A common fish native to saltwater around the Dragon Isles. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

194968.Name: Cerulean Spinefish
194968.Description: A common fish native to saltwater around the Dragon Isles. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

194969.Name: Temporal Dragonhead
194969.Description: A common fish native to freshwater around the Dragon Isles. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

194970.Name: Islefin Dorado
194970.Description: An elusive fish native to the Dragon Isles. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

194971.Name: Crystalized Draconium
194971.Description: Crystalized Draconium, formed under great pressure.

195386.Name: Ayanga's Horn
195386.Description: The horn hums with latent electrical energy.

195468.Name: Shiverweb Silk
195468.Description: A bundle of frozen webbing that grows colder as you hold it.

195543.Name: Riptide Brew
195543.Description: A unique flavor that tastes like... sea water?

197737.Name: Popfizz Punch
197737.Description: Full of fruit flavors, sugar, and something extra.

197739.Name: Happy Trigger Sour
197739.Description: Popular amongst pirates, outlaws, and those of low moral standards.

197754.Name: Salt Deposit
197754.Description: A common reagent acquired by miners and often refined for use by chefs in Dragon Isles cuisine. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

197755.Name: Lava Beetle
197755.Description: A common reagent acquired by herbalists and often refined for use by chefs in Dragon Isles cuisine. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

197845.Name: Silver Scale
197845.Description: An ingot of pure silver forged in the shape of a dragon scale.

197860.Name: Ancient Scrap of Draconic Wisdom
197860.Description: The tattered remains of this scroll give you a glimpse into how ancient dragons understood certain materials.

197862.Name: Primary Security Disc
197862.Description: A device used to keep the Tyrhold forge locked down.

197863.Name: Secondary Security Disc
197863.Description: An additional layer of security in case the primary fell in the wrong hands.

197921.Name: Primal Infusion
197921.Description: This myserious object crackles with elemental energies.

197928.Name: Captivating Cap
197928.Description: A hat to make even the most dull creatures more photogenic.

197946.Name: Dragonforged Poker
197946.Description: A blacksmith tool, used recently for more sinister purpose.

197950.Name: Deepminted Coin
197950.Description: An ancient coin minted in the forges, deep within the vaults of the citadel.

197959.Name: Lavafused Armor
197959.Description: Scraps of ancient armor fused by heat into an impervious shell.

197983.Name: Drakmoss Clump
197983.Description: Skeletons of blue dragons that lay undisturbed in icy climates make the perfect habitat for this rare medicinal moss.

198038.Name: Ancient Titansteel Ingot
198038.Description: Forged by the hand of Aggramar himself, these ingots were used to create the original keepers on Azeroth.

198043.Name: Stealthy Elven Port
198043.Description: A strong flavor that... sneaks up on you.

198044.Name: Whirlwind Wine
198044.Description: Violent shaking has made the contents quite bubbly.

198045.Name: Slam Bam Swill
198045.Description: A rare brew, seldom seen outside of Pandaria.

198070.Name: Tattered Seavine
198070.Description: Fisherman Tinnak was exceptionally good at weaving harpoon ropes, but he went missing a while ago. Last seen in the Upper Frostlands, not far from Camp Antonidas. Bring it to Tavio in Iskaara.

198073.Name: Karha, the Serene Wind
198073.Description: Karha was the staff of Ganmat the Wise, an Ohn'aran windsage who healed countless allies and defeated even more enemies centuries ago.

198074.Name: Josanak, the Certain Victory
198074.Description: Josanak belonged to the undefeated warrior Zaphil. Zaphil always relied on his halberd, just as his clan could always rely on him.

198075.Name: Tsegzaya, the Brambled Bow
198075.Description: Countless arrows from Tsegzaya found their way into both wild game and the enemies of Clan Teerai when Dihar drew the string.

198078.Name: Recruitment Roster
198078.Description: Pages filled with recruitment strategies and instructions to find an artifact at the Nelthazan Ruins.

198079.Name: Orders from Sarkareth
198079.Description: The Aspects are complicit in the Destroyer's crimes. Find evidence of their attempts to control us. Speak out! Resist! - Scalecommander Sarkareth

198091.Name: Slightly Used Recrafted Armor
198091.Description: They won't be needing this anymore.

198132.Name: Recipe: Hoard of Draconic Delicacies
198132.Description: Teaches you how to prepare a Hoard of Draconic Delicacies.

198133.Name: Golden Expedition Compass
198133.Description: The gold looks fake, and it's definitely broken.

198134.Name: Shiny Surveyor Scope
198134.Description: As good as new... should fetch a nice price.

198135.Name: Jeb's Supply Pack
198135.Description: Hopefully it's not just full of underwear.

198137.Name: Esoteric Dragon Shard of Knowledge
198137.Description: Perhaps Khadin could help you unlock the secrets of your profession contained within.

198138.Name: Lightning-Infused Rock
198138.Description: A rock infused with lightning from the Thunderspines.

198185.Name: Handful of Serevite Bolts
198185.Description: A commonly used part for a variety of Engineering crafts. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

198245.Name: Draconium Encased Samophlange
198245.Description: A needlessly complicated omnitool coveted by any Engineer worth their bolts.

198336.Name: Arcane-Infused Quill
198336.Description: The quill twitches with arcane energy.

198343.Name: Soft Ruby Feather
198343.Description: A fluffy feather shed by the ducks of the Ruby Lifeshrine.

198344.Name: Scrap of Fabric
198344.Description: A well-woven, if a little dirty, scrap of fabric. Perfect for making patches.

198345.Name: Glass Bead
198345.Description: A glimmering new eye for Happy Duck.

198349.Name: Stolen Dragonscale Supplies
198349.Description: Stolen goods from the Dragonscale Expedition.

198354.Name: The Black Locus
198354.Description: Like mist on the night sky, the speckle of this gem demands your attention. You should keep it.

198398.Name: Primal Proto-Whelp Scale
198398.Description: Incredibly tough, yet still quite flexible.

198408.Name: Timewalker Notes
198408.Description: A detailed manual on how to use a timewalker staff. Someone has scribbled notes all over it.

198410.Name: Timewalker Staff
198410.Description: An instrument for manipulating time magic and shepherding the timeways.

198423.Name: Shimmering Pigment
198423.Description: A common pigment radiating with possibilities. Milled by players with the Inscription skill. Can be bought and sold on the auction house.

198430.Name: Time Capsule
198430.Description: An ancient box, left behind for those who rediscovered the Dragon Isles.

198443.Name: Titan Temple Relic
198443.Description: A peculiar relic from the Titan Temple.

198448.Name: Dragonscale Expedition Supplies
198448.Description: Various supplies that belong to the Dragonscale Expedition.

198480.Name: The Resplendent Pools
198480.Description: A delicate palette of rose, ruby, and verdant green make up this half-finished painting of the Life Pools.

198482.Name: The Spiral of the Kurgans
198482.Description: Spiral patterns curve around gentle, green hills as white, billowing winds blow trees sideways in this painting of the Ohn'ahran Plains.

198484.Name: Brackenhide's Decay
198484.Description: A heavy green fog hangs over a rotting forest in this painting. The canvas itself smells foul.

198511.Name: Building Materials
198511.Description: The crumbled remains of an earth elemental, calling it building materials is very charitable.

198512.Name: The Great Halls
198512.Description: Barely more than a sketch, tall pillars and bright lights decorate this half-finished painting of the Halls of Infusion.

198513.Name: The Academy
198513.Description: Colorful dragonflight banners hang over a massive wall as drakonids play below in this painting of Algeth'ar Academy.

198514.Name: The Sealed Vault
198514.Description: Great splatters of purple and blue denote bursts of arcane magic in this painting of the Azure Vault.

198515.Name: The Fire Labs
198515.Description: This painting of Neltharus is barely more than vague smudges of red, orange, and black.

198516.Name: Hudson's Final Drawing
198516.Description: An unfinished sketch of Hudson and Ranpiata, their heads close together, smiling.

198517.Name: Pelt of Konkhular
198517.Description: The color of this pelt blends well with the rocks and dirt in the area.

198538.Name: Magically Bound Message
198538.Description: The mysterious parchment emanates a mesmerizing purple colored dust slowly outward, where it dissipates after a fleeting moment.

198540.Name: Golden Claw
198540.Description: A solid gold claw from a scultpure of a dragon.

198564.Name: Time-Lost Relic
198564.Description: A relic pulled from another time.

198597.Name: Time-Lost Possession
198597.Description: A worthless item, but buried in the sand for thousands of years it becomes priceless.

198652.Name: Boku's Belongings
198652.Description: A bag of Boku's belongings, including his totems. One totem is missing.

198655.Name: Boku's Totem
198655.Description: One of Boku's totems stolen by the Nokhud.

198691.Name: Howling Heart
198691.Description: The mote of air pulses in a steady pattern, similar to a heartbeat.

198698.Name: Ridgewater Retreat Orders
198698.Description: Found on the body of the outsider working with the Nokhud.

198701.Name: Inert Vessel
198701.Description: A hollow gem with no visible openings, it feels like it might shatter if you grasp it too tightly.

198715.Name: Runed Draconium Rod
198715.Description: Serves as a runed enchanting rod.

198797.Name: Vial of Mineral Water
198797.Description: 100% natural mineral water bottled directly at the source.

198818.Name: Sneaky Mud Mask
198818.Description: A disgusting slime with a pair of sunglasses stuck inside it.

198834.Name: Scribbled Bark Chunks
198834.Description: Bark-like scroll pieces stolen from the Winterpelt Furbolg.

198868.Name: Small Valdrakken Accord Supply Pack
198868.Description: Contains Dragon Isles Supplies you can use to trade for faction items or progressing skills with faction activities.

198869.Name: Large Valdrakken Accord Supply Pack
198869.Description: Contains Dragon Isles Supplies you can use to trade for faction items or progressing skills with faction activities.

198982.Name: Broken Part: Head
198982.Description: Taken as a trophy, the stone head's cold eyes stare into nothingness.

198983.Name: Broken Part: Arm
198983.Description: Even after being cut down from the statue, the Watcher's arm still holds onto the hammer.

198984.Name: Broken Part: Shattered Orb
198984.Description: Shattered into pieces, the orb's once brilliant light seems to be gone forever.

199064.Name: Vitrified Sand
199064.Description: Some of the golden dust has melted, forming a brittle lattice that shimmers faintly when broken.

199080.Name: Smoldering Phoenix Ash
199080.Description: Once living flame, now merely ash. Perhaps living flame again someday?

199175.Name: Lubbins
199175.Description: Teaches you how to summon and dismiss this companion.

199176.Name: Thick Bear Fur
199176.Description: This thick pelt will keep the people of Three-Falls Lookout warm. Hopefully, someone will get rid of the ticks and fleas before turning these into blankets.

199197.Name: Bottled Essence
199197.Description: Brimming with energy, this essence activates the Engine of Innovation in Valdrakken to create a unique crafting material.

199203.Name: Phoenix Ash Talisman
199203.Description: Only one who truly worshipped the firebird can craft such a haunting memorial.

199646.Name: Imbu Tuskarr Bandages
199646.Description: A collection of bandages the tuskarr of Imbu are accustomed to using.

199704.Name: Artifact Fragment
199704.Description: Not much is known about these artifacts. Hopefully, putting them together will shine light over that mystery.

199822.Name: Impressive Dragon Skull
199822.Description: Proof of slaying any manner of powerful dragon or proto-dragon.

199893.Name: Precious Stone Fragments
199893.Description: Shattered gem fragments from a larger setting of jewels.

199906.Name: Titan Relic
199906.Description: The relic is very old and clearly of titan origin. This is the type of relic that Lead Titan Researcher Sorotis asked you to bring to her.

199917.Name: Dragon Bone Fragment
199917.Description: According to the gnolls, these bones hold special Magic. To us, the bones' mutation could be of value.

200067.Name: Whispering Shard
200067.Description: This shard whispers many compliments into your mind. You are pretty great, aren't you?

200071.Name: Sacred Tuskarr Totem
200071.Description: Stolen from the Iskaara Tuskarr, Elder Poa would reward you if you returned it to them.

200073.Name: Valdrakken Treasures
200073.Description: Contains equipment, supplies, and treasures gathered throughout the ages.

200080.Name: Draconium Nugget
200080.Description: Used to improve Iskaaran fishing net. Bring to Tavio in Iskaara. Can be fished in Dragon Isles highlands, ice holes, or lava pools.

200081.Name: Strong Seavine
200081.Description: Used to improve Iskaaran harpoon. Bring to Tavio in Iskaara. Can be fished in Dragon Isles highlands, ice holes, or lava pools.

200082.Name: Battered Imbu-made Net
200082.Description: Used to improve Iskaaran fishing net. Bring to Tavio in Iskaara. Can be fished in Dragon Isles highlands, ice holes, or lava pools.

200083.Name: Irontree Branch
200083.Description: Used to improve Iskaaran harpoon. Bring to Tavio in Iskaara. Can be fished in Dragon Isles highlands, ice holes, or lava pools.

200084.Name: Salinated Serevite
200084.Description: Used to improve Iskaaran harpoon. Bring to Tavio in Iskaara. Can be fished in Dragon Isles highlands, ice holes, or lava pools.

200085.Name: Khaz'gorite Wire
200085.Description: Used to further improve Iskaaran fishing net. Bring to Tavio in Iskaara. Can be caught with fishing net.

200086.Name: Khaz'gorite-Infused Resin
200086.Description: Used to further improve your Iskaaran harpoon. Bring to Tavio in Iskaara. Can be obtained from BIG fish in the Dragon Isles with an Iskaaran harpoon.

200087.Name: Fallingwater Mote
200087.Description: This viscous liquid is difficult to hold onto.

200093.Name: Centaur Hunting Trophy
200093.Description: Can be turned in to Hunt Instructor Basku in Maruukai to increase your standing with the Maruuk Centaurs.

200108.Name: Irideus' Power Core
200108.Description: Taken from the Halls of Infusion, this device once powered up Watcher Irideus.

200109.Name: Medicative Potion
200109.Description: A pleasant warmth radiates from the opalescent liquid inside.

200110.Name: Whispering Fragments
200110.Description: The whispers from these fragments grow louder the more you collect. Perhaps there is no harm in listening just a little bit.

200117.Name: Watcher's Golden Girdle
200117.Description: Holds many potential secrets of the Titans, metalworking, and most importantly... fashion.

200119.Name: Everblazing Fireheart
200119.Description: They say that Firava's heart grew three sizes that day, thanks to the Primalists.

200122.Name: Temporal Spyglass
200122.Description: Flickers of things past, present, and future overlap as you look through it.

200123.Name: Torrential Lily
200123.Description: Magical water droplets form on the petals and float upwards in spirals.

200124.Name: Disoriented Wishtail
200124.Description: Legends say this rare fish has the ability to grant wishes to those who can catch it speaking.

200125.Name: Stoneheart's Stone Heart
200125.Description: Infused by the Primalists to bestow tremendous power on a mortal.

200129.Name: Kolgar's Pack
200129.Description: Heavy with unused travel gear, enough for two people.

200134.Name: Ohuna Mass-Binding Totem
200134.Description: Carefully crafted by cruel Primalists to imprison the children of Ohn'ara.

200140.Name: Fragments of Fangfall
200140.Description: An ancient sword of unknown power, shattered to pieces during a long-forgotten battle.

200143.Name: Fenistrasza's Skull
200143.Description: Enchanted by the djaradin who slayed the skull's original owner, magma continuously pours from its eye sockets.

200149.Name: Wild Argali Wool
200149.Description: While stained and courser than domestic argali wool, it still functions well to reinforce sitting blankets and tents.

200162.Name: Lost Tuskarr Kite
200162.Description: Small scrolls are attached to different pieces of the kite.

200179.Name: Ruby Lifeband
200179.Description: Crafted by Alexstrasza herself long ago. Holding it, you feel reinvigorated for your next adventure.

200188.Name: Broken Fishing Pole
200188.Description: The fishing line tied to this pole has been snapped, but it might still have some use.

200190.Name: Stuffed Duckling Toy
200190.Description: A small stuffed toy shaped like a duckling, probably left behind by a tuskarr child.

200191.Name: Ottuk Lure
200191.Description: It's a plushie! On a string! What ottuk could resist this?

200200.Name: Earthbound Primordial Core
200200.Description: Captured from a foe by Neltharion long ago, the core still struggles to escape its restraints.

200220.Name: Frozen Tail Darter
200220.Description: A fish that's quite chewy. It's an acquired taste. Supposedly.

200225.Name: Shard of the Greatstaff
200225.Description: A shard taken from Broodkeeper Diurna's greatstaff in Vault of the Incarnates on Normal Difficulty.

200226.Name: Shard of the Greatstaff
200226.Description: A shard taken from Broodkeeper Diurna's greatstaff in Vault of the Incarnates on Heroic Difficulty.

200227.Name: Shard of the Greatstaff
200227.Description: A shard taken from Broodkeeper Diurna's greatstaff in Vault of the Incarnates on Mythic Difficulty.

200258.Name: Arbhog's Horns
200258.Description: Heavy and jagged with many scars from battles old and new.

200273.Name: Saboteur's Map
200273.Description: A detailed map of Valdrakken and the surrounding area. The Seat of the Aspects has a red X crossed through it. In addition, there's a circle around a nearby region marked as the Misty Vale.

200443.Name: Dragon Isles Artifact
200443.Description: A common artifact, but Cataloger Jakes at the Dragonscale Basecamp will reward any artifact returned.

200447.Name: Centaur Hunting Trophy
200447.Description: Can be turned in to Hunt Instructor Basku in Maruukai to increase your standing with the Maruuk Centaurs.

200449.Name: Sacred Tuskarr Totem
200449.Description: Stolen from the Iskaara Tuskarr, Elder Poa would reward you if you returned it to them.

200450.Name: Titan Relic
200450.Description: The relic is very old and clearly of titan origin. This is the type of relic that Lead Titan Researcher Sorotis asked you to bring to her.

200462.Name: Mistyvale Map: Butterfly Garden
200462.Description: A detailed map of Valdrakken, with a red X crossed through the Butterfly Garden. There are notes scrawled in the margins.

200463.Name: Mistyvale Map: Black Market Auction House
200463.Description: A detailed map of Valdrakken, with a red X crossed through the black market auction house. There are notes scrawled in the margins.

200471.Name: Magnetized Splinter
200471.Description: Small splinter of the full stone.

200473.Name: Agitated Fragment
200473.Description: A small vibrating fragment of stone.

200474.Name: Tarasek Pillaged Piece
200474.Description: A piece pillaged from the ruins.

200478.Name: Far-Flung Fragment
200478.Description: A fragment of the larger stone.

200480.Name: Half Swallowed Sliver
200480.Description: A sliver of stone covered in... something foul.

200514.Name: Salve-Soaked Bandages
200514.Description: Thin strips of fabric soaked in a thick salve. Smells like herbs and magic.

200537.Name: Bundle of Primalist Orders
200537.Description: A hastily tied bundle of Primalist Orders ready to be delivered to the commander.

200557.Name: Enchanted Arcana Vessel
200557.Description: Wisps of arcane magic swirl within the enchanted vessel.

200586.Name: Derelict Sunglasses
200586.Description: This fashion accessory is extremely damaged from time spent in the Serene Dreams spa, but perhaps one of the guests will find sentimental value in it.

200587.Name: Leatherbound Expedition Note
200587.Description: The tightly rolled parchment is wrapped in cracked, dyed leather. The initials T.D. are visible across the binding.

200590.Name: Carefully Rolled Message
200590.Description: The note's been rolled so tightly it's stiff, retaining its curled nature no matter how hard you try to unfurl it.

200593.Name: Sealed Expedition Note
200593.Description: Signed and sealed from the Dragonscale Expedition.

200594.Name: Thaelin's Second Favorite Comb
200594.Description: Perfect for even the toughest, dwarven beards.

200595.Name: Odorous Parchment
200595.Description: Whatever was written across the parchment previously appears to have been washed away with water, leaving an odorous smell and watered down lettering behind.

200596.Name: Letter from Thaelin Darkanvil
200596.Description: The letter is written on fresh parchment and stamped with the seal of the Dragonscale Expedition.

200598.Name: Meluun's Green Curry
200598.Description: Generous chunks of fish are immersed in unmistakable flavors of musken cream, greenberry, and hearty spices.

200670.Name: Misttouched Gateway Stone
200670.Description: Cool to the touch. The sound of rushing water fills your ears as you hold onto this stone.

200671.Name: Earthen Gateway Stone
200671.Description: Sharp and rough. The sound of the earth splitting is deafening while holding this stone.

200672.Name: Iceforged Gateway Stone
200672.Description: Your hands want to recoil from the cold emanating from this stone.

200674.Name: Bluebill Meat
200674.Description: A firm slab of duck meat perfect for using in a trap.

200686.Name: Primal Focus
200686.Description: Used to make an Optional Reagent for crafting heroically powerful equipment.

200747.Name: Zikkori's Water Siphoning Device
200747.Description: This device is a hodgepodge of multiple functions, but a large red button makes it easy to use.

201263.Name: Obsidian Journal
201263.Description: A journal kept by one of Neltharion's now deceased assistants.

201264.Name: Neltharion's Notes
201264.Description: Meticulously written by Neltharion's own hand.

201266.Name: Research Tome
201266.Description: Documents the results of a varity of experiments conducted within Neltharus.

201379.Name: Scalewatch Cage Key
201379.Description: A well-worn key for the rebel's cages at Scalewatch Caverns.

201411.Name: Ancient Vault Artifact
201411.Description: This artifact appears to date back to the time of the Incarnates. Lillian Brightmoon of the Dragonscale Expedition would be interested in this item.

201412.Name: Ancient Vault Artifact
201412.Description: This artifact dates back to when the Incarnates were imprisoned. Lillian Brightmoon of the Dragonscale Expedition would be interested in this item.

201415.Name: Temporal Parmesan
201415.Description: Untethered from time, this Parmesan has a nifty habit of materalizing on your pasta ahead of schedule.

201470.Name: Story of a Memorable Victory
201470.Description: That was a good fight! Elder Poa in Iskaara will be interested in listening to the story of that victory.

201471.Name: Story of a Spectacular Victory
201471.Description: That was a majestic fight! Elder Poa in Iskaara will be interested in listening to the story of that impressive victory.

201601.Name: Runed Serevite Rod
201601.Description: Serves as a runed enchanting rod.

201791.Name: How to Train a Dragonkin
201791.Description: It takes the knowledge of dragons to tame their related kin.

201793.Name: Resplendent Gemstone
201793.Description: A curious treasure found within Valdrakken's Great Vault.

201986.Name: Crocolisk Skin
201986.Description: Valued for its oily shine, flexibility, and use in fashionable accessories.

202013.Name: Ruby Recipe Journal VIII
202013.Description: One of many personal journals kept by the chefs of The Ruby Feast, Morsel & Rumiastrasza. It contains experiments, both successful and failed, as well as food doodles adorned with smiling faces.

202017.Name: Liberated Furbolg Artifacts
202017.Description: Scars from recent troubles partially obscure the distinctive, carved lines of furbolg script that cover these beads.

202018.Name: Intact Scribe Stick
202018.Description: Furbolg record everything from important historical events to mundane mercantile interactions on sticks such as these, carving the short strokes of their script directly into the wood. Sonova Snowden would be extremely interested in a find of this caliber.

202023.Name: Spark of Life
202023.Description: This iridescent essence is evidence of the resurgence of the Dragon Isles.

202025.Name: Keg of Ancestral Ale
202025.Description: A keg of Warpath Brewing's finest ale.

202026.Name: Durotar Coast Crab
202026.Description: A wild crab caught on the Durotar coast near the Echo Isles.

202027.Name: Fresh Talbuk Steak
202027.Description: Fresh meat from Talbuks native to Outland. They have been imported especially for the Kosh'harg.

202028.Name: Southfury Salmon
202028.Description: Freshly caught salmon from the Southfury River.

202029.Name: Isle Lemon
202029.Description: Lemons from the Echo Isles. Juicy and tart!

202030.Name: Ground Gorgrond Pepper
202030.Description: Ground peppercorns collected from trees native to Blade's Edge Mountains.

202031.Name: Farahlon Fenugreek
202031.Description: An herb once prized by the Laughing Skull Clan, it is now grown in the Eco-domes of Netherstorm.

202032.Name: Feast for the Ancestors
202032.Description: A feast comprised of cuisine from both Draenor and Azeroth; a worthy offering for the honored dead.

202044.Name: Crystal Focus Fragment
202044.Description: Even shattered, this crystalline fragment thrums with arcane power.

202062.Name: Ash Feather
202062.Description: Shed from the various phoenix in the lava fields near the Obsidian Citadel

202097.Name: Bulging Box of Skins and Scales

202106.Name: Chewed Piece of Journal
202106.Description: The notes are damp, shredded, and nearly unreadable. But a few bits remain.

202180.Name: Pipsee Cheese Snack
202180.Description: This cheese is beyond "aged" by a long shot, but a small worm will love it.

202181.Name: Best-root Tuber
202181.Description: A tough root vegetable with a very pungent smell, just like a Furbolg.

202187.Name: Plagued Flesh
202187.Description: Nonedible. Or rather, ingestion not advised.

202196.Name: Zskera Vault Key
202196.Description: This key can open a door within one of Neltharion's Zskera vaults.

202203.Name: Sending Stone: Protest
202203.Description: Tablet used to send messages over great distances to a receiving stone. Scalecommanders may find this of great interest.

202238.Name: Enforcer Grant's Signet
202238.Description: A simple ring, made up of intertwining metal, with a small stone set, oddly enough, on the inside.

202240.Name: Tome of Fanciful Spheres
202240.Description: This tome describes the fanciful ways to combine spheres and arcane magic.

202241.Name: Tome of Rolling
202241.Description: This tome describes how to manipulate an object to roll at a high speed regardless of physical limitations.

202266.Name: Bag of Spicy Pet Snacks

202286.Name: Warmed Coal

202288.Name: Obsidian Gemstone
202288.Description: A crystal shining with hope for the black dragonflight's future.

202292.Description: A beautiful memento from the depths.

202294.Name: Recipe Pages
202294.Description: A page from a brewing recipe for ale.

202330.Name: Fine-Pointed Quill
202330.Description: All it's missing is a bottle of ink!

202332.Name: Blue Dragon Bedtime Story
202332.Description: The book is entitled Good Night, Azure Span.

202335.Description: From the personal research journal of Adamanthia. Scalecommanders may find this of great interest.

202364.Name: Everburning Ember
202364.Description: Stays warm, even in the coldest conditions.

202394.Name: Fresh Plains Meat
202394.Description: An assortment of cuts and meats from the Ohn'ahran Plains.

202395.Name: Rumble Foil
202395.Description: Bring to a Warcraft Rumble game machine to gain a new mini look!

202399.Name: Stuffed Doll
202399.Description: A stuffed doll for any pet to enjoy.

202400.Name: Soothing Incense
202400.Description: A range of comforting smells for the home.

202402.Name: Bag of Cactus Apples
202402.Description: Contains a young adventurer's hopes and dreams. And cactus apples.

202404.Name: Bite-Sized Ley Crystal
202404.Description: The perfect size for a whelp snack.

202405.Name: Bloody Axe
202405.Description: A flower is engraved on the hilt. The handle is covered in blood.

202414.Name: Tauren Necklace
202414.Description: A simple necklace made of bone and teeth. The engravings display a tauren design.

202415.Name: Unique Headdress
202415.Description: A simple but beautiful headdress in the tauren style.

202619.Name: Mender Supplies
202619.Description: Supplies used by the Healing Wings to treat injuries.

202642.Name: Proto-Killing Spear
202642.Description: Designed to harpoon into a proto-dragon's thick hide.

202643.Name: Soft Sand
202643.Description: Not as coarse as you expected, but still very exfoliating for scales.

202644.Name: Whelp's First Hourglass
202644.Description: Do bronze dragons know how to tell time as soon as they hatch?

202645.Name: Unused Bowl
202645.Description: Left aside in a corner. Surely nobody needs it.

202647.Name: Stolen Goods
202647.Description: Goods looted from the Forbidden Reach.

202690.Name: Decorative Shrubbery
202690.Description: A nicely-shaped shrub with a certain pizzazz.

202694.Name: Loamy Soil
202694.Description: Enriched with nutrients from the Dream.

202695.Name: Ancient Water
202695.Description: The water seems to stay the perfect, refreshing temperature.

202696.Name: Comforting Ducky
202696.Description: A soft plush that has been loved by many hatchlings.

202698.Name: The Dragonkin Voice 4: Might & Right
202698.Description: The dragons have ruled us because theY're stronger than we. But together, in our great numbers, we're stronger than they. If might makes right, then we are right, if we haVe courage to riSe up together. - Instigator Belaphon

202699.Name: The Dragonkin Voice 2: 100 Centuries Abandoned
202699.Description: FoR 100 Years, theY left us alone, while we tended to "their" isles, guarded "their" cities and roads, and kept the peace. TheY haVe repeated that abandonment 99 more times. Should we welcome them with open arms, and obey as before? - Instigator Belaphon

202700.Name: The Dragonkin Voice 3: 100 Centuries Independent
202700.Description: The dragons returned expecting us to Be what we were, but in tHose 100 Centuries, we changed. We grew. We serve them no longer, and are serFs no longer. We've chosen our Path for 10,000 years, and we will do so again. - Instigator Belaphon

202701.Name: The Dragonkin Voice 5: The Rebel Code
202701.Description: And so we Swear one and all to the rebel code. No ruler but one's selF. No purpose but independence. No flight but the flightless. - Instigator Belaphon

202702.Name: The Dragonkin Voice 1: A Dragonkin's Worth
202702.Description: The dragons believE they're worth more than us. That's why Sendrax had to sacrifice herself, foR a dragon egg that might not even be viable. They say she's a herO, but she's really their victim. - Instigator Belaphon

202703.Name: Ephemeral Sand
202703.Description: The grains of sand disappear as you watch it.

202706.Name: Zandali Piri Piri
202706.Description: Small peppers grown in the jungles of Zandalar. They are extremely hot!

202707.Name: Un'goro Coconut
202707.Description: Hard outside, sweet and delicious inside. Loved by gorillas.

202713.Name: Scattered Supplies
202713.Description: Some of Jeb and Tacha's expedition gear.

202873.Name: Drooping Mushroom Cutting
202873.Description: This squishes in your hand as you transfer it to a bag, it will make an excellent poultice.

202874.Name: Healing Draught
202874.Description: 'Pour directly down the throat for maximum effectiveness.'

203012.Name: Viridian Heartcrystal
203012.Description: It is warm to the touch, and hums with a delicate tone.

203013.Name: Niffen Incense
203013.Description: Take a whiff to find the trail!

203183.Name: Sindragosa's Lingering Essence
203183.Description: You hear screams of agony and rage from this small essence. The last remnants of Sindragosa are within, crying out for her torment to be quelled.

203184.Name: Malygos's Lingering Essence
203184.Description: You hear screams of agony and rage from this small essence. Malygos, the former aspect of magic, still remains trapped in his fury.

203229.Name: Snail Slime
203229.Description: Smells... like nothing, actually. To you.

203381.Name: Sealed Letter to Neltharion
203381.Description: A perfumed scent emanates from the letter... centuries old... yet oddly familiar.

203385.Name: Flamesight Rune
203385.Description: The totem dims as you remove this rune. They seem to be attuned to each other.

203386.Name: Box of Leapmaize Crackers
203386.Description: A box of crackers branded with The Roasted Ram.

203393.Name: Spongy Loamshroom
203393.Description: The pores on this mushroom make it ideal for soaking up toxins, for good or for ill.

203394.Name: Elementally Charged Orb
203394.Description: A curious orb-shaped artifact that appears to be of titanic origin. However, a glow of elemental power emanates from within.

203395.Name: Research Journal
203395.Description: The journal is in remarkable condition given its age. The notes within will no doubt keep Dragonscale scholars busy for years to come.

203396.Name: Displayed Armor Piece
203396.Description: This appears to be of black dragon design, but is much smaller than expected. Could it be an early example of dracthyr armor?

203430.Name: Ward of Igira
203430.Description: This series of customized fire protection tools will grant the wielder protection to interact with a Suffusion Crucible. The wards are consumed upon use.

203432.Name: Bag of Spicy Pet Snacks
203432.Description: Only a pet with a very strong constitution could enjoy one of these biscuits.

203433.Name: Wheel of Whelpwhisper Brie
203433.Description: A light buttery cheese with hints of nuttiness.

203442.Name: Snail Slime
203442.Description: Potent slime from an incense snail. This is used as the base ingredient for niffen incense.

203443.Name: Box of Leapmaize Crackers
203443.Description: A box of crackers from The Roasted Ram.

203445.Name: Stuffed Doll
203445.Description: A stuffed doll for any pet to enjoy.

203446.Name: Soothing Incense
203446.Description: A range of comforting smells for the home.

203451.Name: Decorative Shrubbery
203451.Description: A nicely-shaped shrub with a certain pizzazz.

203454.Name: Zaqali Equipment
203454.Description: The accoutrements of ritualistic dragonkillers, meant for ceremony as much as for warfare.

203459.Name: Totemic Ruins
203459.Description: Hacked pieces of petrified wood, iron, and fur.

203463.Name: Atrenosh's Journal
203463.Description: This rugged leatherbound tome contains rants about a soldier's life, violent descriptions of combat, and aspirational writing about weapons.

203473.Name: Geyser Flower
203473.Description: This solitary flower seems to only grow at the base of the Ohn'iri Springs.

203475.Name: Urgent Stormwind Summons
203475.Description: Rather inconspicuous, with a plain, unmarked wax seal.

203651.Name: Saza's Blade
203651.Description: Saza's dagger is still in excellent condition despite being pulled from the corpse of a giant worm.

203653.Name: Vacant Elemental Core
203653.Description: The dormant stone cools rapidly in your hand, waiting to bind to new magical energies.

203654.Name: Zaqali Flame Totem
203654.Description: Brimming with molten lava that glows through cracks in the carved stone.

203656.Name: Odd Device
203656.Description: This device looks like a rod with a crystal on the end, with a handle to hold it by. It looks old, but is slightly familiar to you, like you have seen it in passing. Maybe it's of interest to Voraxian.

203682.Name: Darkened Elemental Core
203682.Description: Hissed voices tickle the back of your mind, half-words and hushed secrets.

203683.Name: Ward of Fyrakk
203683.Description: This series of customized fire protection tools will grant the wielder protection to interact with a Suffusion Mold. The wards are consumed upon use.

203692.Name: Horn Signet of Arrosh
203692.Description: Spattered with spider venom and blood.

203697.Name: Horn Signet of Ekrati
203697.Description: Two words have been crudely engraved inside the metal ring: "Love, Patroclosa".

203698.Name: Horn Signet of Talon Hermin
203698.Description: Nestled adjacent to a nub of writing charcoal.

203701.Name: Neltharion Gift Token
203701.Description: A redeemable gift token, accepted by Prototype Tinker-Tron.

203712.Name: Soft Peafowl Down
203712.Description: The perfect material for stuffing pillows.

203731.Name: Enchanted Bandage
203731.Description: Magically enhanced for use by those who have not learned the art of healing.

203855.Name: Fragile Manaheart
203855.Description: The blossom of this delicate flower is closed.

203913.Name: Blossoming Manaheart
203913.Description: The Manaheart has blossomed and grown sturdy with the magic of the Ancient Bough.

204067.Name: Glowing Crystal
204067.Description: This crystal emits a pleasant teal-colored light.

204069.Name: Sulfuric Crystal
204069.Description: This crystal has a pungent odor.

204070.Name: Magma Crystal
204070.Description: This crystal is warm to the touch.

204071.Name: Head of Kretchenwrath
204071.Description: The remains of this disciple of Fyrakk still radiate with heat.

204085.Name: Zaqali Dragonslayer's Spear
204085.Description: Serrations along the edges of the blade twist backward into cruel barbs. Once it pierces dragon-flesh, it cannot be removed.

204088.Name: Quartzite Spore Bile
204088.Description: It smells about as good as you might expect.

204171.Name: Enforcer Jennive's Signet
204171.Description: A simple ring, made up of intertwining metal, with a small stone set, oddly enough, on the inside.

204173.Description: A simple ring, made up of intertwining metal, with a small stone set, oddly enough, on the inside.

204178.Name: Snailcatcher Net
204178.Description: Specially designed to snare even the slipperiest snails.

204184.Name: Ebon Eviscerator
204184.Description: Ancient, but just as deadly as the day it was forged.

204200.Name: Journal Entry: Experiments
204200.Description: From the personal research journal of Adamanthia. Scalecommanders may find this of great interest.

204208.Name: Primordial Earth Core
204208.Description: Solid and warm to the touch. Its very presence is comforting.

204209.Name: Primordial Flame Core
204209.Description: It shines brightly but does not burn to the touch.

204210.Name: Primordial Storm Core
204210.Description: Constantly changing shape, its movement makes it difficult to handle.

204212.Name: Primordial Water Core
204212.Description: A strange force keeps it from vanishing through your fingers.

204214.Name: Drakefire Amulet
204214.Description: The jewel is surprisingly dull, and the metal oddly light.

204221.Description: From the personal research journal of Adamanthia. Scalecommanders may find this of great interest.

204305.Description: Random research notes bearing Neltharion's signature.

204306.Name: Random Scribblings
204306.Description: Rough drawings by Neltharion... are those the Aspects?

204315.Name: Zaqali Bone Needle
204315.Description: A thin piece of sharpened bone, able to pierce corehound hides without breaking... or melting.
